It'd be nice to have a simple nullToEmpty method for collections that would return an empty collection if the argument is null, otherwise pass through the argument. Something like this:

```
public static <T> Collection<T> nullToEmpty(Collection<T> c) {
    if (c == null) {
        return ImmutableList.of();
    } else {
        return c;
    }
}
```

That way if you were calling an API from somewhere that could return null or empty, and you couldn't change it, you could protect yourself easily even within other expressions:

```
for (Object o : Lists.nullToEmpty(potentiallyNullReference)) { ... }
```

I realize that you could do something like this:

```
Objects.firstNonNull(potentiallyNullReference, new ArrayList())
```

But the nullToEmpty method would avoid constructing the potentially-unused list.

